50|$|A common {{application}} of economizers in steam power plants is {{to capture the}} waste heat from boiler stack gases (flue gas) and transfer it to the <b>boiler</b> <b>feedwater.</b> This raises {{the temperature of the}} <b>boiler</b> <b>feedwater,</b> lowering the needed energy input, in turn reducing the firing rates needed for the rated boiler output. Economizers lower stack temperatures which may cause condensation of acidic combustion gases and serious equipment corrosion damage if care is not taken in their design and material selection.|$|R
