50|$|Feed {{water for}} boilers {{needs to be}} as pure as {{possible}} {{with a minimum of}} suspended solids and dissolved impurities which cause corrosion, foaming and water carryover. The most common options for demineralization of <b>boiler</b> <b>feedwater</b> are reverse osmosis (RO) and ion exchange (IX).|$|R
50|$|In Steam Boilers, sodium {{bisulfite}} {{has been a}} reliable oxygen scavenger in <b>boiler</b> <b>feedwater</b> for approximately 60 years. This compound is characterized as having fast reaction times, low use-cost, years of proven performance, availability. Sodium bisulfite when used in steam boilers has FDA and USDA approvals.|$|R
